parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS module can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to extended stopping distances, loss of vehicle control, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ABS light stays on
the brake pedal travels to the floorboard
the vehicle pulls to one side
the brakes fail to engage
the ABS pump continues to run and drains the battery
the brake pedal feels spongy or soft.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS control sensors can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to extended stopping distances, loss of vehicle control, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brakes fail to engage
the ABS light stays on
the brake pedal feels spongy or soft
the vehicle pulls to one side.

symptoms: The brake pedal travels to the floorboard

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Broken tailgate cables can cause the tailgate to fall open, potentially causing damage to the vehicle or other objects, and may lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Tailgate cables break
tailgate falls open
inability to secure the tailgate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked rear frame can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, leading to potential safety risks, including loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: Cracking or breaking of the rear frame
often just behind the rear axle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty fuel gauge can cause uncertainty about the fuel level, leading to unexpected fuel exhaustion, which can strand the driver or cause accidents.
symptoms: The fuel gauge needle jumps back and forth between empty and full
making it impossible to determine the actual fuel level.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked fuel tank can cause fuel leakage, which can lead to fires, accidents, or environmental hazards.
symptoms: Sudden loud noise
fuel leakage
and the fuel tank collapsing.
